title: Annual Progress Report of the Detroit River International Wildlife Refuge and the International Wildlife Refuge Alliance 2009 Calendar Year
name: annual-progress-report-of-the-detroit-river-international-wildlife-refuge-and-the-internat-d38eb
notes: This annual narrative report for Detroit River International Wildlife Refuge summarizes Refuge activities during the 2009 calendar year. The report begins with a letter from Congressman John Dingell. Followed by an introduction to the Refuge and a summary of habitat conservation efforts.  Information about research and monitoring including common tern breeding pair surveys. Community engagement efforts are discussed along with capacity building efforts. Lastly, upcoming activities and investments are summarized.
